  'submissionChecklist' => 
  array (
    'en_US' => 
    array (
      0 => 
      array (
        'order' => '1',
        'content' => '<p>The document being submitted should be classified in one of the following categories:</p><p><strong>Scientific or technological research article</strong>: A document that presents original and detailed results of research projects. The usual structure consists of four important sections: introduction, methodology, results, and conclusions.</p><p><strong>Article of reflection</strong>: A document that presents research results from an analytical, interpretive, or critical perspective regarding a specific topic, making use of original sources.</p><p><strong>Review article</strong>: A document resulting from an investigation in which the author analyzes, systematizes, and integrates the results of published or unpublished research projects in a scientific or technological field, recognizing and disseminating information about scientific progress and trends in scientific development. These articles provide a careful bibliographic review of at least fifty (50) references.</p><p>[1] Classifications taken from the document General Guide to the Updated Index of Colombian Serial Publications in Science and Technology (<em>Orientaciones generales de la actualización del índice de publicaciones seriadas científicas y tecnológicas colombianas</em>), Colciencias, 2002.</p><p>Articles in any of these categories must include a section presenting conclusions.</p><p>All research articles must include descriptions of methods, results, and sources.</p>',
      ),
      1 => 
      array (
        'order' => '2',
        'content' => '<p><strong>Authors must also provide the following:</strong></p><p>When submitting an article, authors must also send the following documents:</p><p><em>Cover page:</em> The cover page must include the name of the article in Spanish and English, the name of the author or authors, their institutional affiliation indicating city and country, source of financing for the research project, a brief summary of the author or authors’ CVs (maximum four lines per CV), and their institutional email addresses. The author should also indicate if the article has been presented at any meeting or congress or whether it was written for a presentation.</p><p><em>Abstract and keywords:</em> The author or authors should attach an abstract of the article in both English and Spanish, each comprising no more than one hundred twenty (120) words. The abstract should be succinct and should very briefly present the goal, the methodology, the results, and the conclusions of the article in such a way that the reader will get a full idea of the document’s contents at its first reading. A maximum of five key words should be provided in both English and Spanish to facilitate the indexing of the article.</p><p><em>Authorization to publish</em>: The author or authors should complete the authorization to publish, sign it physically or electronically, and send it to the journal. The authorization to publish is available to authors on the journal’s webpage. This authorization is a required step in the submission of a manuscript. </p>',
      ),
      2 => 
      array (
        'order' => '3',
        'content' => '<p><strong>General instructions for submitting articles</strong></p><p>Length: maximum 30 pages (8,000 to 10,000 words including bibliographical references)</p><p>Margins: 3 cm (1.2 inches) on each side of the page</p><p>Spacing: double-spaced, including block quotes. Do not insert tabs or extra spaces between paragraphs. Do not use page breaks.</p><p>Font: Times New Roman, 12-point</p><p>Page numbers: lower right corner on every page</p><p>Title: In Spanish and English. If the document is written in another language include a Spanish and an Enlglish translation of its title.</p><p>Authors: the complete name of the author or authors should appear beneath the title of the document.</p><p>A short biography of the authors (maximum of 4 lines each) should be provided in a footnote, including institutional affiliation, current position, and e-mail address.</p><p>Footnotes should be for the purpose of clarification, not to provide bibliographical information, except in the case of a complementary reference.</p><p>The abstract should be 120 words long, and should be provided in both Spanish and English. It must provide the main idea of the text and information regarding the methodology of the research, its development, and the conclusions that were reached.</p><p>References should be provided in a list at the end of the article.</p><p>Section headings should be consecutive, using only three levels formatted in the following manner:</p><p>1. <strong>Title 1</strong></p><p>1.1. Second level subtitle</p><p>1.1.1. Third level subtitle</p><p>2. <strong>Title 2</strong></p><p>If figures or tables are included, a maximum of two colors per figure is recommended. It is the author’s responsibility to obtain all permissions and rights to include materials or illustrations that come from other sources.</p>',
      ),
